Package: acme.toolkit
Title: Reference Architecture for S7 + targets + Quarto + Shiny R Packages
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mickaël", "Canouil", , "pro@mickael.canouil.dev", role = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3396-4549"))
  )
Description: A minimal, domain-neutral R package that demonstrates a reusable
    architecture for analysis tooling: an S7 object model with search-path
    fallback, a config-driven targets pipeline rendered from a Whisker
    template, parameterised Quarto reporting backed by a branded multi-format
    extension, and a modular Shiny application. The toy domain is generic
    tabular analysis (summary statistics) so the package builds with no heavy
    dependencies.
